12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3260 of Title 70, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. By July 31, 2028, and by July 31 each year thereafter, each
17 institution of higher education within The Oklahoma State System of
18 Higher Education shall electronically submit to the Oklahoma State
19 Regents for Higher Education the following information for the
20 preceding academic year:
21 1. The number of full-time faculty employed by the institution;
22 2. The number of full-time faculty members who have been
23 awarded tenure;
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1782 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 3. The number of part-time faculty including adjunct
2 instructors or employees; and
3 4. The number of graduate assistants employed by the
4 institution including the number of courses taught by each graduate
5 assistant.
6 B. By September 1, 2028, and by September 1 each year
7 thereafter, the State Regents shall electronically submit to the
8 Governor, the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker
9 of the House of Representatives the information submitted pursuant
10 to subsection A of this section.
11 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3213.1, as
12 amended by Section 2, Chapter 312, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
13 Section 3213.1), is amended to read as follows:
14 Section 3213.1. A. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
15 Education shall make educational program resources at institutions
16 in The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education available to the
17 people in the Ponca City area. This The program shall be known as
18 the University Center at Ponca City.
19 B. The State Regents shall draw upon the educational programs
20 of institutions best suited to provide the kind of educational
21 programs needed and shall, in pursuance of Article XIII-A of the
22 Oklahoma Constitution and appropriate statutes, set the standards of
23 education as they relate to the programs operated to assure that
24 credits earned by students will be fully accepted at institutions of
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1782 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 high er education to which the students may transfer the credit to
2 apply toward an educational study objective.
3 C. The State Regents may establish appropriate funds and
4 accounts, including a revolving fund, in the Office of Management
5 and Enterprise Services for servicing the fiscal operations of the
6 University Center at Ponca City. The funds and accounts shall be
7 subject to the direct supervision, management, and control of the
8 board of trustees created by subsection D of this section. The
9 people locally shall provide suitable physical plant accommodations
10 for the University Center at Ponca City.
11 D. There is hereby created a board of nine (9) trustees to be
12 appointed by the Governor by and with the consent of the Senate to
13 serve as the administrative agency for the University Center at
14 Ponca City. The board shall be a body corporate and shall adopt and
15 use an official seal. The board so created shall have the authority
16 to submit a budget annually to the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
17 Education, administer monies budgeted by the State Regents, provide
18 educational facilities, recommend courses and programs to be offered
19 by participating institutions, select a chief executive officer
20 whose duties include the general coordination of approved programs
21 and services, and the selection of other appropriate nonteaching
22 personnel. The board of trustees is authorized to expend all monies
23 allocated to the University Center at Ponca City as may be necessary
24 to perform the duties and responsibilities imposed upon the board by
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1782 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 this section. For purposes of acquiring and taking title to real
2 and personal property from sources other than state appropriations,
3 the board is authorized to enter into contracts and to adopt rules
4 and regulations pertaining to such actions. The initial nine (9)
5 members shall serve their terms for the period to which originally
6 appointed, in numbered positions having dates of expiration
7 identical to the dates of expiration of the original appointments:
