SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1782 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Position No. 9. The term of office of one member shall expire
2 on June 30, 2021, and each nine (9) years thereafter.
3 The board shall organize and elect a chair, vice-chair vice
4 chair, and secretary annually.
5 E. The board of trustees may, except as provided for in
6 subsection F of this section, establish and maintain plans for
7 tenure and retirement of its employees and for payment of deferred
8 compensation of employees and may provide hospital and medical
9 benefits, accident, health, and life insurance and annuity contracts
10 for employees and pay for all or part of the cost with funds
11 available for payment of its operating expenses.
12 F. Beginning January 1, 2027, the board of trustees shall not
13 have the authority to establish and maintain plans for tenure of
14 employees hired January 1, 2027, and thereafter. The contract of
15 any employee hired on January 1, 2027, and thereafter shall not
16 exceed five (5) years.
17 G. The board may establish with the State Treasurer any
18 accounts as are necessary to operate retirement, deferred
19 compensation, or benefits plans for its employees. The accounts
20 shall be revolving funds not subject to fiscal year limitations.
21 Funds deposited in the accounts may be invested in any of the types
22 of instruments in which the State Treasurer is authorized by law to
23 invest.
