3 SECTION 9. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 4413, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 4413. A. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
6 Education shall have authority to establish a two-year community
7 college in Tulsa County to serve Tulsa County and surrounding area,
8 if provision is made locally for the donation, to the State of
9 Oklahoma, this state of a suitable site for the college, which shall
10 be known as the Tulsa Community College and shall be an integral
11 part of The Oklahoma State System of Higher Education;, and shall be
12 entitled to the same privileges and be subject to the same laws as
13 other member institutions of such State System.
14 B. After the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education have
15 acted to establish the Tulsa Community College, there shall be
16 created the Board of Regents of the Tulsa Community College, which
17 shall consist of seven (7) members, to be appointed by the Governor,
18 by and with the advice and consent of the Senate. Four members of
19 said Board shall be residents of Tulsa County. Appointments shall
20 be to numbered positions on the Board, and the terms of members of
21 the Board shall be as follows:
22 Position No. 1. The term of office of one member shall expire
23 on the 30th day of June, 1969, and each seven (7) years thereafter.
24
